    "description": {
      "gm": "<p>It can be purified in a Hard Level 12 DC based ritual (tbd)</p>",
      "value": "<p>The Twashtar is an ornate, emblazoned weapon with a gilded hilt and a djezet blade gleaming with a holy light. Mandalic patterns seem to play in its reflection and offers a serene calm. It bears a beautifully decorated scabbard and a grip covered in silks and gems. The base of the blade is intricately carved into a mandala.</p>\n<p>The Twashtar is a +2 Greater Striking Holy Djezet Kukri; as an instrument of the divine, it also bears the additional properties of being cold iron, silver, and ghastmetal, and strikes true against the unholy, triggering any weakness to Good/Holy. It actively rejects being attuned by those who are unholy or profane.</p>\n<p>When wielded by a Divine spellcaster, any minions or Eidolons they summon gain the relevant material and traits to their unarmed attacks, in addition to the effect of the Holy rune.</p>\n<p>The blade of this footâ€‘long knife curves inward and lacks a cross guard at the hilt.</p>"
